From 367095c4bfe0fa1ed16813f366a81766a67d9425 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Huang Lee <Putin.li@rock-chips.com>
Date: Sat, 9 May 2026 18:25:30 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] video: rockchip: add multicore RGA vendor driver (OOT,
 develop-6.6)

Out-of-tree driver lifted from rockchip-linux/kernel develop-6.6
(drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/), carried as OOT against mainline
v7.1 alongside the rcawston VEPU580 OOT driver.

Path A per rga_path_decision.md (2026-05-09): the mainline V4L2 RGA
path (drivers/media/platform/rockchip/rga, even with the Pengutronix
RGA3 v5 series applied) cannot today express librga's multi-source
alpha composite in one ioctl chain. Until V4L2 m2m grows multi-input
single-output blend AND librga gains a V4L2 backend, the vendor
/dev/rga ABI is what userspace (librga.so / scale_rkrga / vpp_rkrga
/ overlay_rkrga / FFmpeg --enable-rkrga) actually speaks.

Source: https://github.com/rockchip-linux/kernel/tree/develop-6.6
        drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/
HEAD at extraction: 1ba51b0 (2025-08-08)

This commit produces the file shape only:
  - drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/{Kconfig, Makefile, *.c, include/*.h}
  - drivers/video/rockchip/{Kconfig, Makefile} stubs sourcing rga3/
  - drivers/video/{Kconfig, Makefile} hooks descending into rockchip/
  - DT: replaces the mainline rga@fdb80000 (V4L2 rockchip-rga compat)
        with vendor-compat rga2_core0; adds rga3_core0 (fdb60000) +
        rga3_core1 (fdb70000) + per-core IOMMU nodes.

Compilation against mainline 7.1 is NOT attempted here. Forward-port
work (dma-buf/iommu attach/clk_bulk/dev_pm_opp drift, vendor-only
header refs in rga_drv.c) happens in a follow-up patch.

Module name remains rga3.ko (per rga3/Makefile obj-$(CONFIG_ROCKCHIP_MULTI_RGA)
+= rga3.o); rk1_config must set CONFIG_ROCKCHIP_MULTI_RGA=m and drop
CONFIG_VIDEO_ROCKCHIP_RGA, otherwise mainline's V4L2 rga driver will
fail to bind (compat strings replaced) but its module will still build.

Signed-off-by: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
